  array (
    'en_US' => '<p>With the advent of globalization and the spectacular growth of Information Technology, the international Business has entered into new vistas, with multidimensional complexities and opportunities ranging from the core sector to expanding service sector. This has necessitated scientific cultivation of skills, knowledge and application of managerial art, information management, development of macroeconomic model. With this backdrop, the NIT Durgapur, a premier institute of national importance under the MHRD, GOI organized the 1st International Conference on Business &amp; Information Management (ICBIM-2012), which provided an interactive platform for exchanging views among academicians and corporate executives on emerging issues. Research papers presented in the conference have been published in international proceedings.</p><p>Enriched with the success of 1<span>st</span> ICBIM, there was a remarkable elevation of the status of 2<span>nd</span> ICBIM (held in 2014, 9<span>th</span>-11<span>th</span> January) with the technical sponsorship from IEEE Kharagpur Section.</p><p>The 3<span>rd</span> Conference, namely 3<span>rd</span> International Conference on Business &amp; Information Management (ICBIM-2016) will be held from 9<span>th</span> to 11<span>th</span> January 2016 with the presentation of keynote address by distinguished professors from abroad and India, along with scholars from academia and corporate sectors. The conference will cover topics related to Business Management, Computer Applications and Information Management, Petroleum Management, Oil Economics, Mineral Economics, Communicative English, Economics.</p>',
